						               													<description>2321: The largest city on the moon of Klathea&amp;#10;52-F is under attack as waves of alien ships&amp;#10;suddenly appear in the sky above it. You are&amp;#10;unable to even fire one proton blast before fire&amp;#10;rains down onto the city.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this small 1-card game you are the military leader of the capital of Klathea 52-F.&amp;#10;Your task is to distribute the resources in a way that will defend the city, and destroy the attacking alien fleet.&amp;#10;To do this each turn you will be drawing a random colored cube, which you will have to assign to one of the city's military facilities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are three types of cubes, each with it's own use:&amp;#10;White cubes - are the raw materials needed to perform any action.&amp;#10;Red cubes - are the ammunition needed to destroy the attacking ships.&amp;#10;Blue cubes - allows you to strengthen the force field protecting the city, and heal the city itself when the force field is compromised.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These cubes will be placed on action spaces, which in turn form action rows.&amp;#10;Once an action row (compromising of action spaces of different colors) is full, you remove those cubes from the row and perform the actions linked to that action row.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After you place all of your cubes, the enemy gets a chance to attack you.&amp;#10;But the more damage you deal to them, the less firepower they have.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Defeat the second wave of aliens, and you win!&amp;#10;But let the city's health reach 0, and you are decimated...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
